OOC is the result of a 1982 Government directive that created a joint venture company for oil exploration in Chinese territory, and a part of the \u201cinner sanctum\u201d of the top 50 Chinese state-owned companies. At the same time, rising concerns over fossil fuel dependency have prompted the Chinese to pass a law that aims to have wind power provide 10 percent of total energy supplies in the next five years. The new plan, described as ambitious by experts, will see the present 0.01 percent of power grid contribution by wind- power electricity increase substantially through infrastructural investments and price fixing for solar- and wind- generated electricity. Sources: The New York Times, July 7 and 20, 2005 41 The global business turnover in energy products was estimated at US$2.4 trillion in 2000 (Evans 2002). The bulk of this, between US$ 1.7 and $2 trillion, featured in trans-border trade, much of it in oil, oil products and gas. Assuming an annual growth rate of 2.5 percent and taking into account the steep increases in global oil prices since 2003, the current volume of globally traded energy likely exceeds US$3 trillion a year, making energy the largest component of international trade. This does not include trade in energy services18 (the numerous technology, skill, capital and managerial inputs) that go into each link of different energy chains, from exploration to delivery at the point of end use. These are valued at about US$100 billion a year based on projected energy investment needs alone for the period 2000-2030 (IEA 2003). 18 \u201cEnergy services\u201d as distinguished from \u201cenergy goods\u201d in international trade definitions. 42 | Trade in Environmental and Energy Services and Human Development: Contributing to Well-Being, Growth and Access for All Table 2: Select Energy Indicators Traditional fuel Electricity GDP per CO2 emissions \u2013 consumption consumption unit of share of Country per capita energy use world total (% of total energ